ogical theories of state formation, while showing how labor movements and other forms of popular mobilization shaped the origins of the regional states-system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aMiddle East Studies. 4aPolitics -- International Relations. 4aPolitics -- Middle East. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804768023zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804768023423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804768023/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles